title: Birmingham Christmas parade axed as budget reined in
text:
Tweet 
The colourful procession of festive floats traditionally celebrates the switch-on of the Christmas lights and is a popular highlight of the city’s calender. 
The city council says it costs £50,000 to stage the event and it could only continue to be held if sponsorship was found. 
Despite efforts, no sponsors could be secured to ensure the event could o go-ahead this year, but bosses said they would continue to look for potential backers so the parade could return in the future. More Birmingham entertainment news
